Bye 2023!!! The year of the awakening, the year I realized so many things… lessons learned, healing ❤️‍🩹 journey, new city, new beginnings, letting go and letting God do His thing! Surrendering to what I cannot control and owning up to my decisions and my doing. 

It’s crazy how sometimes life keeps you so busy that the distractions are real, takes you off course and you end up in the middle of nowhere. Sometimes it’s the Nowhere where you actually are found and go back to the basics… the basics of God, the basics of life and what matters, the basics of knowing who will actually catch you when you fall versus just watch you fall, to the basics of knowing that there will be people that wrong you, talk bad about you, and judge you, learning to just be still and pray for them as they do not know better.

I understand that God parted the Red Sea He didn’t remove it, but He made way to get through it! That has been my 2023 🙏🏼 He parted the sea for me, and I went through it! 

I’m ready for you 2024! To be filled with Joy, Love, Honor, Friends, Family and the Basic things of Life! 

Thank you to my 4 angels that keep me running, walking and crawling forward! I love you David, Daizy, Josiah and Jeremiah, you guys are my motor! Thank you to those that caught me 🤪 when I was falling you’ve never failed me ♥️ and to all those that sprinkled so much unconditional love and support! Those that prayed for me. I’m so grateful for you all!
Grateful for these moments 2023
